From f669be27ed2e210fd59eb90796d315eddbda8523 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan Carpenter <error27@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 09:47:25 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 54/71] ntfs: add missing error code in ntfs_mft_record_alloc()

Return -ENOMEM if the kmalloc() fails.  Don't return success.

Signed-off-by: Dan Carpenter <error27@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>
---
 fs/ntfs/mft.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/fs/ntfs/mft.c b/fs/ntfs/mft.c
index aa72ea376..e00829034 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs/mft.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs/mft.c
@@ -2503,6 +2503,7 @@ int ntfs_mft_record_alloc(struct ntfs_volume *vol, const int mode,
 			folio_unlock(folio);
 			kunmap_local(m);
 			folio_put(folio);
+			err = -ENOMEM;
 			goto undo_mftbmp_alloc;
 		}
 
-- 
2.54.0

